defaultCan you give examples of criminal offences which fall on the threshold – e.g. for which sentences of, say, anything from three to six years, might be given? (i.e. a situation in which two people convicted of the same offence may get different sentences such that one is disenfranchised and the other is not)
defaultThe range
default of sentences for apparently sim
defaultilar offences is wide. An early guilty plea will earn a 33% discount. 
defaultGenuine 
defaultremorse will get an additional reduction
default. Aggravating factors can make a large difference: 
defaultprevious conv
defaulti
defaultctions; 
defaultyoung or elderly victims; premeditation
default etc. In aggregate, these aggravating and mitigating factors can play as large a part in determining sentence as the charge.
